Map<K,V>
public class FilteredMap<K,V>
extends AbstractMap<K,V>

A map whose keys must be allowed by a specified key filter. The filtered mappings are kept in the same order they occurred in in the original map.

Author:
Scott Martin

Constructor Detail

FilteredMap

public FilteredMap(Map<? extends K,? extends V> originalMap,
                   Filter<? super K> keyFilter)
Creates a new filtered map including only the elements in originalMap whose keys are allowed by the specified keyFilter.

Filtered maps maintain an entry set whose entries occur in the same order as they occurred in the original map.

Parameters:
originalMap - The map to draw this map's elements from.
keyFilter - The filter that decides which keys from the original map should be represented in this filtered map.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - If keyFilter is null.
See Also:
Map.putAll(Map)
